main event: A fast moving, elliptical, silver object the size of a nickel was seen traveling southerly faster than a jet for 10-15 seconds.
interesting points: The object was seen during the daytime.
The sighting trend suggests it was not a meteor.
There was not enough data to conclusively determine the nature of the object.
The object was observed by a civilian Ground Observer Corps (GOC) post.
The sighting occurred over Van Nuys, California.
sighted object: Elliptical, silver object the size of a nickel
